6455, "(fr)$b Masyaf $b Secure $b Net - $b Message $b Received
$b Sender: $b Al-Da'wa (authenticated $b x8t8oo2g569: timestamp discrepancy)

I wrote this message before you decided to leave the Red Room. You will read it as you awake from the dreamscape, ready to fight.

The future is determined by its past. Know the state of the board and the rules of play, and you know what is yet to come. Predicting the actions of one woman is difficult, but not beyond our $f CASSANDRA mainframe, or beyond me.

This talent for simulation also tells us where and when to strike to alter the course of the war."

6456, "(fr)You want answers. What we want. Who you are.

You will learn these things. They are secondary. You must master that which makes you $f Fedayeen: the capacity for violence, and the knowledge of when to use that violence. You must be ready to commit atrocities if necessary, and you must nonetheless understand that they are atrocities.

Nothing is true. All actions are permitted. But not all actions are correct. In every moment, you must find the shortest path to our ultimate goal. Ruthlessness, mercy, torture, succor, hatred, compassion: these are all tools, to be deployed as they are needed.

Our single overriding goal is the survival of mankind. The $f Council $f of $f Elders has made it clear to us that if the $f United $f Earth $f Federation is lost, that objective will fail. We intend to learn why."

6457, "(fr)Recent events left you critically damaged. You feel that our prospects in this war are also crippled. But we have a new asset.

We count amongst our ranks four $v Vasudan pilots, stranded in Sol after they helped destroy the $r Lucifer. Their appreciation of the $r Shivan threat led them to help found the $f Fedayeen.

Days before the Fall of Jupiter, they left Sol on the invitation of $v Emperor $v Khonsu $v II. Once they reached $v Aldebaran, these $f Fedayeen completed a pact that began with secret radio transmissions between Alpha Centauri and Earth thirty years ago. The $f Hammer $f of $f Light has come to our aid. We have access to a fanatically loyal intelligence network built deep into the fabric of the $r GTVA's military.

The critical moment of the war is upon us. The Elders have at last authorized us to act without restriction."

6458, "(fr)Your coordinator and fellow operators will prepare you for your first mission.

You are no longer Ubuntu$semicolon some would say no longer human. Succeed in this sortie, and you will become one of us.

Al-Da'wa"

6459, "(fr)$b MASYAF $b PRIORITY $b COMMUNIQUE
Personal Distribution, Eyes Only 
FROM: $f Thorn $f (cassandra4393)

I'm Thorn. Dreamscape info doesn't always stick, so here's the short version: I handle tactical prep for your wing and liase to the $f CASSANDRA simulation unit. Don't ask to see $f CASSANDRA. It won't happen.

We're still hunting the $r mole inside the Federation that tipped Steele off to your meeting with the Vasudans. We believe this same mole also leaked details of the attack on the $r Carthage. We know that this mole must be positioned highly, perhaps close to $f Admiral $f Netreba. I'll keep you updated.

I have no news for you about $f Captain $f Lorna $f Simms. But I know about your list. It would be my pleasure to help you reach the bottom."

6460, "(fr)$b MASYAF $b PERSONAL - $b EYES $b ONLY - FROM: $f Kovacs

You're about to become a Fedayeen operator. Whatever else you might become in this life, you'll always be a Fedayeen operator. It marks you.

The awful things you've heard are true. If the Federation is all the Elders hoped humanity could become, well, we're all that they feared we might have to.

Falconer, Vidaura and I will fly with you. If you talk, we'll listen. If you break, we'll pick up the pieces. There are no ranks between Operators. Performance is what matters. Bringing you in was a gamble, Laporte. But what isn't?

Prep is underway for our first op together. "

6461, "(fr)$b Ainsarii $b Strike $b Fighter $b (Stealth)
$b Pilot's $b Reference - $b Opening $b Abstract

The $f Ainsarii is the latest descendant of the stealth fighter program initiated by Galactic Terran Intelligence before the Isolation. Produced on eccentric-orbit asteroid workshops, the $f Ainsarii combines the speed and agility that Fleet pilots demand with next-generation weapons systems such as the $f Sidhe molybdenum shrapnel weapon and the $f UX $f Accelerator light antimatter massdriver.

The Ainsarii carries a full stealth suite, from low-observability hull design to active countermeasures. Only $r Charybdis or $v Setekh AWACS, or the Terran $r Aurora fighter, can consistently detect it.

$f Ainsarii pilots must treat their large, vulnerable ship as the assassin it is: making quick, lightning attacks and retreating to repair and rearm."

6462, "(fr)$b Reference $b Continues

The $f Ainsarii serves as a testbed for several experimental technologies now entering broad deployment.

You will be authorized to carry two such flight systems.

The Cellular Ammunition Pack replaces one of your primary weapon mounts with fast-load packs for your internal secondary bays. Fire it to reload your secondaries.

The Repair System includes a reserve of coagulating polymer similar to that used by support ships. When selected, it will drain your ship's weapon energy and gradually scab over damaged armor, repairing your fighter."

