9394, "(fr)The Prometheus retrofit was an attempt to manufacture the mighty Prometheus cannon without access to the technological and industrial base of Sol. Shortages of vital materials were used as a public excuse for simple failure of institutional knowledge - after an awkward attempt to hybridize technology from the older Banshee cannon, the Prometheus R failed to perform to acceptable specifications due to huge issues with the onboard power supply. The weapon could not outperform the Subach HL-7. This proved a mild boon when thousands of units were seized by the NTF Rebellion, stranding them with a cheap but only marginally effective primary weapon. Conspiracy theorists often seize on this as proof that the NTF was a GTVI false-flag operation to disrupt Vasudan economy superiority."

